                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                <head>No. 386.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bassett</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-07-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 22, 1874</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 207.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi> With reference to your 326 of the 9th instant,
                    acquainting the Department with the honors paid to the United States and to the
                    President, by President Domingue and by the diplomatic representatives at Port
                    au Prince, on the national anniversary of the Independence of the United States,
                    I have to request you, in the name of the President, to convey to President
                    Domingue his acknowledgments for the friendly sentiments toward the United
                    States expressed in his note, a copy of which accompanied your dispatch.</p>
                <p>I am &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
